cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a new approach for landmark localisation in 3D medical volumes using a Convolutional Neural Network (CNN). This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) categories. The approach also involves multi-task learning (cs.AI) and principal component analysis (cs.MM) to improve localisation accuracy and localise multiple landmarks. The use of a CNN for landmark localisation also involves regression and classification tasks, which are common in neural networks (cs.NE).
